==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1705. From {{suffix|Acadia|an|t2=one that is|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈkeɪ.di.n̩/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈkeɪ.di.n̩/|/əˈkeɪ.dʒn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪdiən|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or pertaining to [[Acadia]], its people, or their language or culture. {{defdate|First attested in the early 19th century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|geology|lang=en}} Of or pertaining to the [[Acadian epoch]].

====Usage notes====
